Steps.Message: Update at 11:20 - Engineers are working to divert power around the underground cable fault. Businesses usually have back up plans for emergencies, but by clicking this link https://bit.ly/2Y6Z16K you can find some answers to frequently asked questions from business customers. If you are a domestic customer and need further support, please call us on 105. We will get your power back on as soon as we can and will update you when we have more information.

We became aware of this power cut at 08:32. We’re sorry for any disruption this may have caused you. We didn’t know in advance there would be a power cut, but now that we know, our teams will do everything they can to get your power back quickly. Engineers in our control room have switched some customers power back on in your area. To get everyone’s power back on we may need to attend to investigate and make repairs. We’ll continue to update you until everyone’s power is back on.
Steps.Name: We are restoring customers automatically

Steps.Message: We have engineers on their way. As this is affecting your area, they will not need to attend your property. Rest assured once they arrive, they’ll work as quickly as is safely possible to get your power back on.
